    affiliation: "Faculty of Environmental Earth Science, Hokkaido University"
keywords:
  - parallax correction
  - satellite imagery
  - remote sensing
  - atmospheric science
  - cloud top height
  - geospatial processing
abstract: >
  pyparallax is a Python library for performing parallax correction 
  on satellite imagery, particularly useful for correcting the apparent 
  displacement of clouds and other elevated features in meteorological 
  satellite observations. The library includes optimized Fortran 
  extensions for computational efficiency.
